      • checkCollision

        public void checkCollision(App gameboard,
                           TileObject enemyTile,
                           java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,TileObject> surroundingTiles)
        Check if this enemy collides with other game objects, and updates behaviours that needs to change upon collision.

        The enemy reflects horizontally or vertically as it hits corresponding sides of a wall. The sides of a wall is determined via the 8 tiles surrounding the enemy, categorized into 4 sides. The chance of a wall being present depends on how many tiles on 1 side are hit (performs reflection for greater than 2 tiles: 2=very likely a wall, 3=definetely a wall).

        The enemy only reflects once until it reaches a different tile to avoid it getting stuck reflecting back and forth in the same tile.

        Parameters:
        gameboard - the current gameboard (i.e.App)
        enemyTile - this enemy's tile
        surroundingTiles - the 8 tiles surrounding this enemy

      • attack

        public void attack(App gameboard,
                   Player player,
                   TileObject enemyTile)
        Defines the attack beahviours of this enemy. All enemies in normal state causes Player.die(App) upon collision when player in soil area. Enemies in vulnerable state respawns to another soil tile upon collision with player. See respawnTile(TileObject[][]).

        All enemies in normal state triggers red path to start propogating from the path tile that was hit. See Player.initialPropogate(TileObject).

        Parameters:
        gameboard - the current gameboard (i.e.App)
        player - the player in this game instance
        enemyTile - this enemy's tile
